<p>When I create a static class, the static should be implicitly applied, not merely required, on all members.  Being forced to put static on every member in a static class is silly redundancy for a language that strives for clarity via brevity.  I should not have to write</p><pre>static class Utility {
public static int SomeFunc() {...}
}</pre><p>I should be able to just write</p><pre>static class Utility {
public int SomeFunc() {...}
}</pre>

